description:
&lt;p&gt;THIS POST IS AVAILABLE TO ALL APPLICANTS WHO CAN DEMONSTRATE RELEVANT PROFESSIONAL REGISTRATION, EDUCATION TO DEGREE LEVEL OR ABILITY TO DEMONSTRATE EQUIVALENT LEVEL OF KNOWLEDGE&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;What&#39;s so special about PCLS....?&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We asked our staff members to highlight what was so special about our team here are some of the responses.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&#39;We are a friendly mixed team of nurses, psychologists, psychiatrists and admin staff.&#39;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&#39; We work in a positive forward thinking environment&#39;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&#39;The job is fast paced and no day is ever the same&#39;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;Primary Care Liaison is a specialist mental health assessment service in Wiltshire&lt;/span&gt;.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will join a highly experienced and dedicated team who pride themselves on collaborative working , whilst providing interventions for a range mental health presentations. We cover a large geography with a diverse population as such we are continually adapting our service provision. We take a modern approach to working remotely and recently introduced assessments and interventions via &#39;Attend Anywhere&#39;.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We invest in all our team members and will support you to develop new skills and training opportunities such as &#39;brief interventions&#39;, &#39;Non medical prescribing&#39; and &#39;management&#39;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If you hold an appropriate professional registration (i.e. mental health nursing, social work, OT) and would like to experience being part of our dynamic team please apply!&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Experience in later life functional care would be advantageous but not essential.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:   Patricia Hanlon, Team manager / Matthew Collis, Senior Practitioner 01722 820372&lt;/p&gt;
